<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A local species endemic to the Sierra de Amambay in Paraguay and neighbouring parts of Rio Grande do Sul in Brazil, apparently always growing in cerrado. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">PARAGUAY. Amambay</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rojas</emphasis>
in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hassler</emphasis>
10620 (BM); 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">K. Mizoguchi &amp; T. Sano</emphasis>
1139 (MO); Chiriguelo, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. Schinini &amp; M. Dematteis</emphasis>
33482 (CTES, FCQ), 33647 (FCQ, CTES); 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Krapovickas et al.</emphasis>
45907 (CTES, K); Cerro 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Corá">Cora</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Krapovickas &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cristóbal">Cristobal</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
44958 (CTES, F, FCQ); ibid., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. Soria</emphasis>
5740 (CTES, FCQ); ibid., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N. Soria &amp; E. Zardini</emphasis>
1952 (FCQ). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">San Pedro</emphasis>
: Rancho Laguna Blanca, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
F. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="González">Gonzalez</normalizedToken>
&amp; M.J. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
757 (FCQ), 817 (FCQ), Yaguarete Sustainable Forest, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. Zardini &amp; L. Guerrero</emphasis>
43282 (MO, PY).
</paragraph>
